description: It begins here, the three-part saga that exposes all the secrets, rewrites what you thought you knew, and takes our young heroes to hell and back... literally!  How did the Black Marvel acquire the means to recruit the kids who would be Ricochet, Hornet, Prodigy and Dusk? How did such a long forgotten man think he could recapture the glory of his 'Golden Age'? And what's the price they all must now pay for the bargain he struck?! Believe us, after this story, nothing's ever going to be the same for our teen team!
name: Raising Hell's Children, Part 1 - The Devil's Due

description: The Black Marvel was a desperate man. And in the Marvel Universe, Mephisto is the devil you make your desperate deals with! Now, he's come to collect, and only Ricochet, Dusk, Hornet and a rejuvenated Prodigy stand in his way. It's an 'Inferno' all their own as our rookie heroes face their worst fears and demon hordes in a race across the Underworld!
name: Raising Hell's Children, Part 2 - The Devil You Know

description:
Fate-filled final issue! Ricochet, Hornet, Prodigy and Dusk have the opportunity to save the Black Marvel's soul, the soul of their mentor and manipulator, the man whose machinations tore apart their lives, the man they hate so very much. They have the power. They can save him. But will they?
 
Contains a mini story about Zane Whelan named "Fast Lane, Part 1 of 4 - Media Blitz!"
name: Raising Hell's Children, Part 3 - The Final Cut
Human Interest and Slyde into Destiny

description: It's another pair of stories set in the world of the web-slinger! A young man must grapple with a life-altering choice in "PREVENTATIVE MEDICINE" by Tom McLaughlin and Scott Kolins. Then, in "6TH" by Brandon Thomas and Ale Garza, Spidey must cope with both the Vulture and his own spider-sense!
name: Preventive Medicine and 6th

description: Two more stand-alone stories of the wall-crawler by new and upcoming writers! First, Robert Kirkman (CAPTAIN AMERICA) teams with his INVINCIBLE partner Cory Walker for a story of true love found amidst the carnage of a hold-up. Then, Allan Jacobsen and C.P. Smith (the creative team on the upcoming NEW INVADERS series) weave a tale connecting the web-spinner to the legends of Native America!
name: Love Withdrawl and The Old Ways

description: First, the all-Johnson team of Kim "Howard" Johnson and Staz Johnson relate the story of a hostage crisis at the Daily Bugle. Then, Martin Sweeny tells of a security guard whose life is changed when a robbery goes awry, Spidey-style!
name: Retraction; Facing Down the Darkness

description: Two new tales of Spidey's world by two new writers and the best artists in the business! First, Spider-Man must grapple with the grim spectre of defeat in a story by Sheldon Allen and Jim Cheung! Then, witness the life story of a man who'll one day be known as "Thug #1" by Scott Gimple and Stuart Immonen!
name: The Agony of Defeat and Thug #1

description:
Best-selling “Dune” novelist KEVIN J. ANDERSON and superstar artist ALE GARZA bring you the swashbuckling story of your favorite interstellar pirates – THE STARJAMMERS! Young Tolo Hawk is a fresh-faced cadet in the Union Corps who dreams of a long and glorious military career. What will happen when he comes face to face with the lawless, rough and ready Starjammers? 
   
Aboard the diplomatic yacht Kurnit Corona, wide-eyed young cadet Tolo Hawk travels with his proud father to the royal planet Kinshaa, capital of the Union of Intelligent Races, to begin training in the Union Defense Corps. Also on the ship is the beautiful Princess Sabra, who will soon ascend to the throne left empty by the assassination of her father, and her advisor, Verdian Terce, a member of the secretly evil Committee. 
In private, Terce communicates secretly with his master Anazar Prime, while both of them consume a dose of the illegal narcotic Hyrax. Verdian reveals that the Kurnit Corona carries a large shipment of Hyrax onboard, and that the Committee intends to murder Princess Sabra before her coronation and blame the act on the space pirates known as the Starjammers. 
Alarms sound on the Kurnit Corona: the ship has been boarded by the vicious Starjammers, the half-cyborg Raza, the amphibious Ch'od and a crew of treelike aliens called Thorns, led by the terrible Captain Kalyx. Urging his father to stay safe in their cabin, Tolo takes up a ceremonial pistol and prepares to face the pirates...
name: The Cadet And The Corsairs, Part 1

description:
Tolo risks his life to protect a beautiful Princess from the Starjammers, but are they his real enemy? 
   
The pirate sweep through the ship, and Raza guides the pirates to the diplomatic yacht's cargo bay, where they discover the secret cargo of Hydrax. Thiw contraband cargo is the real reason they have attacked the ship. 
With help from her bodyguard, Princess Sabra is whisked to safety in an escape pod. Tolo and his father are not so lucky, however. Trapped in a malfuntioning pod, Tolo watches in horror as his father is killed by the monstrous Thorn commander. Moments after his escape pod launches, the pirated brutally destroy the Kurnit Corona, killing everyone aboard. Tolo's pod is captured and taken aboard the pirates' ship, the Starjammer. All alone, Tolo prepares to fight to the death...
name: The Cadet And The Corsairs, Part 2

description:
Young Tolo Hawk has been through hell, and as far as he’s concerned, the interstellar pirates called the Starjammers are responsible for every minute of it. So what could happen to change his opinion of these uncouth pirates? This naïve cadet and these gruff corsairs may have more in common than they thought… 
 
Despite his best efforts not to be captured alive. Tolo is taken captive aboard the pirate ship, where he is forced into menial labor. Raza, though gruff and uncompromising, takes the kid under his wing, saving his life when the other Thorn pirates want to kill him. When Raza tries to convince the patriotic cadet that his Union Defense Corps have committed atrocities against other races, Tolo refuses to believe him, though a seed of doubt is planted. 
When the Starjammer encounters and raids a U.D.C. cargo ship, Tolo begs Captain Kalyx not to kill the innocent crewmen, and Kalyx grudgingly agrees. The crewmen take their story back to Princess Sabra who, manipulated ba Anazar Prime, issues a decree that the Starjammers are to be stopped at all costs. 
Soon afterward, two U.D.C. attack vipers close in on the Starjammer. The space pirates look doomed, but before the battle can begin, a tremendous energy storm blasts the vipers and the Starjammer, leaving them all dead in space. Seeing his chance to escape, Tolo makes his move...
name: The Cadet And The Corsairs, Part 3

description:
Young Tolo Hawk sees his opportunity for revenge when trouble befalls his captors. But will he be willing to take advantage of this chance…especially once he finds out what their real motives are? 
 
The Starjammer hangs dead in space for hours. Without light to fuel their photosynthesis, the plant-based Thorns begin to die. Eventually, only Captain Kalyx is left alive. Tolo escapes from his cell and rampages through the ship, killing a few Thorns himself along the way while evading Raza and Ch'od. At last, he finds a dying Captain Kalyx on the bridge. Before Tolo can kill him, though, Kalyx explains to Tolo what the aim of the Starjammers really is, to rescue the hundreds of thousands of hyrax seeds kidnapped by the U.D.C.. Hyrax is not simply a drug, it is the seed of the Thorns. The Comittee has been hording and consuming countless unborn Thorn Children. 
Shocked by the knowledge that the U.I.R. could commit this act of genocide, Tolo begins to wonder if his original perception of the Starjammers as heartless killers is correct. He decides to give them the benefit of the doubt for now and help get the ship back to safety...
name: The Cadet And The Corsairs, Part 4

description:
The time has come for both Tolo and the Starjammers to decide where their loyalties lie – and what they’re going to do about it! 
 
Back at the Starjammers' base on the Thorn homeworld, Tolo is greeted with hostility, particulary from the base commander, Hepzibah. Just when he is about to be judged before the grove of Thorn elders (former Thorns who have now taken root as trees), the base is attacked by Union Defense Corps Forces. They burn the grove, kill many Thorns, and carry away the remaining hyrax seeds. Tolo is thunderstruck by the genocidal actions of the U.D.C. and vows to stop them, though not trough violence. He decides that they should go directly to Princess Sabra and let her know what is going on in her government.
name: The Cadet And The Corsairs, Part 5

description:
The Starjammers have declared war on the Union of Intelligent Races…but how do they plan to win? The answer might just be in young Tolo Hawk’s hands. 
   
Tolo and the Starjammers crash Princess Sabra's coronation to expose the actions of the Committee in the assassination of her father and their use of Hyrax seeds, which are actually Thorn embryos, as a drug; Anazar Prime takes a Hyrax seed to battle the Starjammers but it kills him; With the Thorn pirates now as allies and Princess Sabra left with a political mess to clean up, Tolo decides to stay behind and help while the Starjammers blast off to further adventures.
name: The Cadet And The Corsairs, Part 6

description: Continuing directly from the pages of AVENGERS #82-84! The super-soldiers of the greatest generation stand united once again! But the conflict between these new Invaders and the mighty Avengers threatens to escalate into all-out Armageddon!
name: Once an Invader (Part 4)

description: Overview Soldiers, Super Heroes, Sentinels of Liberty since the Second World War---they're the INVADERS, and they're back in this all-new ongoing monthly from writer Allan Jacobsen and artist C.P. Smith. Jim Hammond, the original Human Torch, returns to lead the INVADERS on a covert mission to stop a mysterious terrorist cell from resurrecting the monstrous evil slumbering in the depths of the Arabian Sea.
name: To End All Wars (Part 1 of 3)

description: A secret society of madmen and monsters, a battleship with world-threatening weaponry, the return of a forgotten hero, and the birth of a new heroine are just the beginning! New Invaders: jump on the ride.
name: To End All Wars (Part 2 of 3)

description: Because you demanded it! It's all-out action aboard the Battleship Infiltrator as the greatest villains of WWII return to fight the Inaders for control of the 21st century's deadliest weapon!
name: To End All Wars (Part 3 of 3)

description: Hollywood Writer Allan Jacobsen and Fan-Favorite Artist C. P. Smith cordially invite you to England for a blood-thirstingly good adventure, chaps! Der Blutsauger, the Children of Blood. Vampires. Skinheads. The ancestral curse of the Falsworth Bloodline has returned, and this time they're out for SPITFIRE'S blood! Featuring the MIGHTY DESTROYER and the V-BATTALION!
name: Blood (Part 1 of 2)

description: Journey into darkness with the INVADERS as they storm the subterranean stronghold of the deadly BARONESS BLOOD to save the lives of SPITFIRE's family! If you only buy one comic this month, make it two and try NEW INVADERS, one of Marvel's best new titles! By superstar-in-waiting C.P. Smith and King of the Hill producer Allan Jacobsen.
name: Blood (Part 2 of 2)

description: "Oil & Water". Enemy Of The State tie-in as Wolverine guest stars. The New Invaders versus HYDRA! Namor versus Wolverine! And a nation hangs in the balance.
name: Oil & Water

description:
In the tradition of MARVELS and from the creative team behind ULTIMATE SPIDER-MAN!
The Daily Bugle has never been a friend of the super heroes of NYC, but with profits down and the newspaper's survival on the line, J. JONAH JAMESON turns the heat up a notch! Meet the Bugle's new team of super hero investigative journalists - Jessica Jones, Kat Farrell & Ben Urich - as they dig up the dirt on the city's most famous heroes ... NO MATTER THE COST or WHO GETS HURT!
name: Thin Air Part 1

description: Overview Pooling their resources, the Daily Bugle's new team of super hero investigative journalists - Jessica Jones & Ben Urich - are pulled into a mystery that hits VERY close to home.
name: Thin Air Part 2

description:
"THIN AIR" PART 3 (OF 5)

Spider-Man joins forces with Jessica Jones, Ben Urich and Kat Farrell to bring the Green Goblin to justice!
name: Thin Air Part 3

description:
"THIN AIR" PART 4 (OF 5) GUEST-STARRING SPIDER-MAN AND THE GREEN GOBLIN! BY THE CREATORS OF "ULTIMATE SPIDER-MAN!"  
Spider-Man guest-stars!!  
As tensions between the Bugle and Norman Osborn mount, what side will Peter Parker take? Featuring the Ben Urich moment you've been waiting for for twenty years!!
name: Thin Air Part 4

description: Overview The downfall of Norman Osborn - the shocking conclusion to the story that rocked the Spidey-verse! Straight from the pages of Marvel Knights Spider-Man! See how it happened! Luke Cage vs. the Green Goblin! Right here!
name: Thin Air Part 5

description:
Overview Jessica Jones and Luke Cage's lives have been destroyed by the events of the Secret War, so what is Jessica going to do about it? Fans of Secret War – feel The Pulse as it pounds out more gritty intrigue even as it welcomes a new artist: award-winning comics superstar Brent (RISING STARS, ASTRO CITY) Anderson!

Guest-starring: Captain America, Luke Cage, Iron Fist, Nick Fury and many, many more.
name: Secret War Part 1

description: The mighty Thor, now the undisputed Lord of Asgard, has made a decision to get more involved in the affairs of mortals. Asgard, the fabled city of the Norse Gods, floats above New York City, and the US government is not happy about. The Amazing Spider-Man attempts to council a god, but an attack from below only proves Thor's point that the time has come for immortals to once again guide their mortal brethren to enlightenment.
name: With Great Power

description: The time of "The Reigning" has begun. The Lord of the Aesir has brought forth Asgard, home of the Norse Gods, to guide mortal man to a better future. But first take a look at time long since past when the Thunderer was but a young godling still learning the ways of mortal man. Plus, meet Thialf, the orphaned boy who would be taken in by the gods.
name: Realization

description: The Dark Gods have returned to Asgard to conquer! This time they will find the task a much more difficult one as it is now Thor the mighty Thunder God who rules here. But who is the true mastermind behind their attack? The answer does not sit well with the new Lord of Asgard.
name: 100 Days

description: Imagine a world where men can walk on walls, a little girl can walk through walls, some can read minds, and gods walk the earth. Dan Jurgens and Joe Bennett take a look at what it means to have faith in the Marvel Universe.
name: To Reach Eternity

description: The Lord of Asgard addresses the United Nations, Loki and Amora the Enchantress find that they may have finally achieved their life's long dreams, and Zarrko the Tomorrow Man predicts bad tidings to come. Plus, the most unexpected outcome to a confrontation between Thor and the Absorbing Man you could ever imagine.
name: Reason

description: Thor has come to Midgard to offer his godly guidance, but not everyone is on board with what the Thunder God has to offer. One man is willing to do anything to discredit the Thunderer. Even stage his own death.
name: Resistance

description: Dan Jurgens and his cadre of talent artist bring you a tale of imagination as told by Volstagg the Stout. In this unique issue each every turn of the page reveals a 2-page spread, each rendered by a different artist.
name: The Gardener

description: After taking on the role as ruler of Asgard, Thor has relocated his legendary home to float directly over New York City. But how will the citizens of the world -- including Thor's former allies in the Avengers -- react when a host of self-styled Gods decides to intercede in the affairs of man?
name: Standoff, Part 1

description: The year is 2026 A.D. A homeless teenager makes a startling discovery - the long lost magical Hammer of Thor! Is that crazy old man going on and on really the Odinson? Is that shady looking man in the trench coat really Loki, the Lord of Lies? D.J. intends to find out.
name: The Substance of Things Hoped For

description: Jake Olson, a valiant young man considered by many to be the best EMT in the city, was once the earthly avatar of the God of Thunder. Even though he no longer possesses the power of a god, Jake is still a force for good and he proves everyday by helping his fellow man. Meanwhile, Thor goes on a mystical sojourn where a clandestine meeting with the All-Father will teach him more about the Odin Force and his place in the universe.
name: Discovery

description: The Lord of Asgard attends a meeting with his fellow Sky Fathers: Zeus, Osiris, Yu-Huang, Vishnu, Brahma, and Shiva. Here he will put through a test to see if he is worthy of taking his father's seat at the table. Meanwhile, Volstagg has been appointed a most sacred task - the protection of Tarene the Designate. She who is key to the unification of the universe. He'll find it a task easier said than done.
name: Sons of the Father

description: Thor continues to try and find the wisdom his father used to rule the Golden Realm. Meanwhile, what is Zarrko the Tomorrow Man up to and what secrets does he know about the Odinson's future?
name: Flames of Passion

description: One man vows to move heaven and earth to get his son, a devout Thor fan, to college. As fate would have it, fortune does not smile upon him. But when he bares witness to divine intervention, Lars must rethink his stance on faith.
name: The Follower

description: Thor, Lord of Asgard, is using the vast power at his command to heal the sick and feed the hungry. As his influence over the world of mortals increases so does the number of his followers. Thorist, once thought of as nothing more than a cult, have grown into legion and the religion of Asgardianism is growing everyday. So where does the Prince of Lies, Loki fit into all this? Read on and find out.
name: One Night

description: Has Thor finally crosses a line. When the Lord of Asgard uses the Odin Force to resurrect a small child the world and other pantheon lords look on in horror and dismay.
name: Frenzy

description: In the aftermath of last issues events, more and more people are turning against Thor. America declares war on Asgard! Could this be the beginning of the end predicted by Zarrko the Tomorrow Man?
name: Cometh the End

description: The US government has declared all out war on Asgard. They tried to murder the Thunder God with a nuclear explosion and they've invaded the scared halls of the Golden Realm with their stormtroopers. To say that the Lord of Asgard is displease would be an understatement. Featuring the death of a major character and Thor's fall from grace.
name: The Gates of Hell

description: The time of "The Reigning" is upon mankind. Seventeen years ago New York City and Asgard was destroyed as a result of war between man and god. Now in the year 2020, Thor and his royal consorts rule the world and intend to lead mankind into the future. Whether they like it or not.
name: Earth 2020

description: It is many years since the Aesir took control of Midgard. Now Earth shall be reconfigured to meet the vision of Thor, Lord of Asgard. Plus, a shocking last page you have to see to believe.
name: Earth 2170

description: The Aesir, the fabled Norse Gods, now rule mankind. But there are those who will ever oppose them. Plus, Thor reveals his master plan for his mortal subjects. Featuring the daughter of the Scarlet Witch. And introducing Magni, the son of Thor.
name: Paradise

description: Thiafi learns some hard truths about his king. Truths that may cause him to rethink his stance on things. Plus, Magni meets Jordah's mother.
name: Undertow

description: In light of recent revelations, Thiafi's faith in the Lord of Asgard, and his beloved friend, Thor has been shaken. Plus, Thor's own son, Magni, learns some hard truths of his own about how mortal man feels about the Aesir's rule.
name: Paradise Lost

description: Take a look back at the year 2020 and bare witness to the last stand of the heroes of Earth. Captain America, Vison, Doctor Strange, Hulk, Thing, and Wolverine mount one final, albeit, desperate assault in an attempt to topple Thor's rule.
name: The Betrayed

description: Led by the daughter of the Scarlet Witch, mankind makes it final attempt to dethrone the Lord of Asgard. And they just might succeed to for Thiafi, Thor's closest friend and confidant has decided that the Odinson is no longer fit to rule. Is this the end of "The Reigning?"
name: Forever Branded

description: Magni, the son of Thor, discovers the missing hammer, Mjolnir. Proving himself worthy the youthful god raises one of the most powerful weapons in the universe in triumph. And, somewhere deep in space...Desak, the Destroyer of Gods, awakens.
name: Realization

description: The climax of Thor's reign as the ruler of Asgard begins NOW! The action heats up and the heavens tremble as all the Thunder God has built comes to ruins, and those closest to Thor betray him!
name: Challenge

description: Only one can wield Mjolnir, the mighty mystic Uru hammer. Will it be Thor, or his son Magni? And must the son kill the father in order to restore peace on Earth?
name: The Reckoning

description: Will the devastating attack of Desak, Destroyer of Gods, on the empire Thor has built unite the Odinson and his son, Magni? Who will wield the unstoppable hammer, Mjolnir?
name: Slipstream

description: Confronted by his son Magni to lift Mjolnir, and attacked by Desak, Thor finally realizes the error of his rule over Earth and sees Loki once more for what he is, The Trickster. With the help of Tarene the Lord of Asgard will look for a way to atone and set things right.
name: Letting Go

description:
RAGNAROK PART 1

It's the beginning of the end of the world for the Gods of Asgard, and only Thor and his Avengers allies might be able to stave off that fate- but does the God of Thunder even want to? Thor- Disassembled starts here!

In the land of the dwarfs, Odin and his brothers formed the earth as gods. After forming the Earth, Odin visits three dwarfish craftsmen to make him a weapon. They make Mjolnir a war hammer out of parts of the sun. Loki came into Asgard when Odin killed his real father and took Loki in as an orphan. Odin always favored Thor over Loki and this made Loki jealous. Odin gives Thor Mjolnir and this enrages Loki. Wanting to get a weapon equal to Mjolnir, Loki sets out to search for the mold which was used to make Mjolnir.

After the three craftsmen dwarfs died, they were honored by the gods and put to rest in a tomb. Thor and a few friends: Hogun, Volstagg, Fandral, Sif, Baldur, and Amora head for the tomb to pay their respects. As they are mourning their deaths, they are attacked by Loki and a few of his goons (Hyrm, Ulik "The Invincible", and Fenris "The Wolf"). During the fight, Loki's crew knocks down a stone pillar and it strikes both Thor and Amora "The Enchantress" to the ground. Amora is feared to be dead and Thor is dazed. He staggers to his feet only to be met by Hyrm and they begin to battle. After a short period of time, Hyrm and Thor's hammers strike each other which causes an explosion. Mjolnir is broken. He shouts, "Avengers Assemble!". Back in Midgard--Earth--Captain America and Iron Man are busy saving people from a burning building when they get the call...
name: Ragnarok Part The First

description:
RAGNAROK PART 2

The immortal city of Asgard suddenly seems quite mortal, as Captain America, Iron Man, and Thor discover. The God of Thunder must lead what is left of the Asgardians into their (likely) final battle!

Hearing Thor's call, Captain America and Iron Man come to his aid in Asgard "home of the gods". Walking through a battlefield they survey the dead and try to figure out what happened before they arrived. How does Thor not know? Hmm... Sifting through some of the rubble Captain America notices that there's a young boy trapped under a pile of wood. He frees the rubble and swaddles the kid. They begin questioning him as to what happened on the battlefield. Immediately Thor assumes that it was the work of trolls but the kid corrects them--It was Loki and his goons.

Just as the kid advises them of their doing another battle ensues with Loki and his crew. Thor calls Loki out and challenges him to a one-on-one. Loki declines and sends Ulik and Fenris after them. Captain gets bit by Ulik during the fight. Loki and friends retreat after a long battle.

Afterwards Thor, Iron Man, and Captain America head for town. They arrive and find themselves in the middle of a funeral for a fallen soldier in the battle. The funeral is for Balder, Thor's brother. Thor is upset and calls for his mother Frigga. Thor gives a motivating speech for all those that still remain in his service, he seeks revenge for all of the injustice.
name: Ragnarok Part The Second

description:
RAGNAROK PART 3

Ragnarok appears to have come for the gods of Asgard, but will Thor be their savior, or its architect? In search of new wisdom, the Thunder God must repeat the ordeals of Odin, and the price may be too terrible for even an immortal to pay!

Volstagg, Hogun, and Fandral come into Alfheim--home of the light elves--looking for safe refuge from battle carrying the injured Sif. They are greeted by a few elves and they rush to their aid. As soon as they meet up, they look to the sky to see Naglfar--the ghost ship approaching. They fear their doom.

In the present day, Volstagg, crumbles a statue to find Thor resting and recovering. Thor immediately notices that there is something different about Volstagg. Volstagg is skinny, he's as trim as a goat! Volstagg reports to Thor, who begins to believe that he was the last surviving of his kind. Volstagg tells of the last two battles and of the falling of all of his friends (Sif, Hogun, Baldur, and Fandral).

Thor and Volstagg begin to travel back to the battlegrounds to survey the area. On their journey back, they begin to recruit other survivors, orphans, and volunteers to their cause. After making it back to the main battlegrounds, Thor begins to recognize some of the fallen. Specifically, Kurse and Vidar--his brother. As they are tending to the wounded they are attacked by Fenris the wolf. During the fight, they are joined by Valkyrie "Defender of the Earth". Shortly after joining the battle, Valkyrie is struck down and killed. Once she was vanquished, another foe joined in the festivities--Durok "the Demolisher". He gets stabbed by Sif's sword (Dragonfang) at the same time Thor is launching Fenris with his fists. Thor hurrys over to finish off Durok and then begins to take on Fenris for a third time when he is joined by Beta-Ray Bill...
name: Ragnarok Part The Third

description:
RAGNAROK PART 4

Beset on all sides by treacherous foes from his past, the God of Thunder leads the tattered remnants of the forces of Asgard on a desperate quest, as the Realm Eternal burns. Beta Ray Bill takes over leadership for Thor is his almighty absence!

Beta-Ray Bill comes and saves the day. He demolishes Fenris the Wolf and calls on any other demons to face the same challenge and fate. Nobody else dares to take that challenge and begins to leave. Beta-Ray Bill states that the Odinpower called him there and that is how he knew that Thor was in trouble. Thor orders Volstagg to lay down Sif and count the dead while Beta-Ray Bill attempts to heal Thor to the best of his ability.

After Thor feels a little better he calls upon Beta-Ray Bill to stay behind and rule Asgard in his stead. Thor wishes to visit Midgard for a "period of time". Thor announces this to his people and makes his way to do a little soul searching. Thor finds a temple and begins to meditate. He is approached by a ghost who brings riddles and a challenge. The ghost mentions that Odin had once came to this same place for some soul searching of his own. This ghost notifies Thor that in order for him to progress he would have to die....
name: Ragnarok Part The Fourth

description: What makes a god? Is it birthright, is it happenstance, or is it in the making? Thor finds out the hard way as he seeks answers on how to face the coming end of his people. Thor struggles with the knowledge that his father knew these end-times would come--and yet did nothing to prepare for it. Does that mean Thor should embrace this ultimate doom he and the gods of Asgard were born to face, or like a true warrior, fight against it to the bitter end? To find his answers, Thor must walk the path of his father and embark on the hero’s journey - the journey into mystery! He must surpass his father’s deeds in the search for knowledge and pay the ultimate price.
name: Ragnarok Part The Fifth

first_appearance_teams.name: Those Who Sit Above in Shadow

team_credits.name: Those Who Sit Above in Shadow

description:
RAGNAROK PART 6

It's the end of all that is, and you've got a ringside seat for the last day of the Norse Gods, as Thor struggles to break the God Cycle once and for all! You must read this, True Believer!

Allies are falling. Asgard has just hours to live. And Thor has to find a way to...let it happen?
name: Ragnarok Part The Last

first_appearance_teams.name: Those Who Sit Above in Shadow

team_credits.name: Those Who Sit Above in Shadow

description: Andy Diggle (THE LOSERS) and Enriqué Breccia (LOVECRAFT) join forces to bring new life to the swamp. Stripped of Alec Holland's human conscience, the Swamp Thing seeks to restore balance to the natural world, but at what cost to his daughter Tefé, his wife Abby and John Constantine?
name: Bad Seed

description: The new series returning the classic Swamp Thing to his roots continues. Abby tries to reason with the fearsome Swamp Thing, only to discover that the all-powerful elemental has turned his back on humanity once and for all. While the Swamp Thing is determined to make Tefé pay for the damage she wrought on the Green, Tefé finds herself drawn halfway around the world to confront her mysterious benefactor...
name: Bad Seed Part Two

description:
Tefé is reluctant to embrace the godlike destiny which Sargon has promised her ? until she discovers the wonders of the "morphogenic field," otherwise known as The Red, where all flesh is one. But does her father, the Swamp Thing, truly covet and fear her power over the flesh? And if so, to what extremes would he go to ensure she never becomes a threat to him?

General Notes

While Tefe's shirt on the cover should probably read "Psycho Bitch", it seems covering up the last two letters with a coat wasn't enough as the letter following T clearly is not a C and it leaves it looking more like the shirt says "Bith".
name: Bad Seed Part Three

description: The uneasy truce between the Swamp Thing and his daughter Tefé finally explodes into all-out conflict. Nature is not human-hearted, and the Earth Elemental will not allow his human heritage to stand in the way of his ascension to godhood. But John Constantine has plans of his own — plans which are personified by the shambling zombie of the man formerly known as Alec Holland.
name: Bad Seed Part Four

description: The penultimate chapter of the 6-part "Bad Seed," plus a free 8-page preview of THE BOOKS OF MAGICK: LIFE DURING WARTIME. The Swamp Thing and his human daughter Tefé battle for possession of ultimate power ? a battle that draws in every living thing on Earth. Only one of them will walk away from this alive...but which one? While John Constantine can only watch from the sidelines, Sargon the Sorcerer finally shows his true colors.
name: Bad Seed Part Five

description: Sargon's trap is sprung, and John Constantine must play the most dangerous game of his life. Alec Holland is reunited with the Swamp Thing, only to face some murderous consequences and the death of a loved one. Now he must make the ultimate sacrifice: die to save the world, or remake it in his own image.
name: Bad Seed Conclusion

description: Swamp Thing’s mind is tearing itself apart. When an unsuspecting cryptozoologist arrives in the Louisiana bayou, Swamp Thing drags the scientist deep into his pit of mental torment. What neither knows is that lurking in the dark lies an even greater threat — one bent on mounting Swamp Thing’s head in a macabre trophy room.
name: Missing Links Part 1

description: Nissing Link Part 2 of 2. Acclaimed artist Richard Corben (Hellblazer) concludes his 2-part SWAMP THING stint in unforgettable fashion! The safari to bag a Swamp Thing takes a shocking twist when Alec's true enemy reveals himself ? and he's more powerful than even Alec could have imagined. But that conflict pales when a reminder of Swamp Thing's past seeks him out in the bayou.
name: Missing Links Conclusion

description: New regular writer Joshua Dysart (Violent Messiahs, THE DEMON: DRIVEN OUT) debuts with "Love in Vain," Part 1 of 4. Swamp Thing's long-forgotten act of kindness toward a young girl unleashes a hellish disaster. When the girl, now grown, performs a clumsy juju ritual to summon her "swamp spirit," she gives Hell's most dangerous soul the escape route to Earth he's been waiting for.
name: Love in Vain Chapter 1

description: In "Love in Vain" Part 2 of 4, it's the return of Anton Arcane...and this time, he's in love. Arcane and his demon-lover consummate their relationship, spreading a terrible infection through the Green and into the swamp. But as Swamp Thing tries to cure the disease, Arcane plans a hellish fate for the town of Houma.
name: Love in Vain Chapter 2
